## ğŸ”¹ How to Answer This in an Interview (Perfect Structure)

### âœ… Short Answer (30 seconds)

> â€œHigh-Level Design defines the overall system architectureâ€”services, communication, scalability, and tech stack. Low-Level Design zooms into a single service and defines the classes, interfaces, relationships, and design patterns used to implement it. HLD answers *what*, LLD answers *how*.â€

